      <hedline>
        <hl1>In Our Own Backyard</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Wendy Mesnikoff letter praises Bill McKibben's May 3 Op-Ed article for point out need for more than 'feeble' response to global warming (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Three cheers to Bill McKibben (Op-Ed, May 3) for pointing out the need for more than a ''feeble'' response to global warming.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Three cheers to Bill McKibben (Op-Ed, May 3) for pointing out the need for more than a ''feeble'' response to global warming.</p>
        <p>Bill Clinton, as President of the world's leading emitter of global-warming pollution, does not have to travel to the ''crumbling edge of the West Antarctic Ice Sheet'' to be inspired to action. What he saw along the flood-ravaged Red River should have been enough. If not, a visit to Texas, where there was an outbreak of dengue fever, or to the coasts, where beaches are disappearing, should be.</p>
        <p>WENDY MESNIKOFF  Hastings-on-Hudson, N.Y.  May 5, 1997</p>
        <p>Greenhouse Theory Inflates Human Significance</p>
      </block>
